This is an R Markdown document for ggplot2 plotting, which supports continuous updates.

require(ggplot2)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
require(reshape2)
## Loading required package: reshape2
JV.theme<-   theme(plot.title = element_text(color="black", size=20, face="bold.italic"),
                   axis.title.x = element_text( face="bold",size=14),
                   axis.title.y = element_text(color="black", size=14, face="bold"),
                   legend.title =element_text(face = "bold", size = 14, color = "black"),
                   legend.text = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
                   axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold",size=14),
                   axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", size=14),
                   panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
                   panel.border = element_rect(fill = "NA", colour = "black", size = 2)
                   )
tropical=  c('darkorange', 'dodgerblue', 'hotpink', 'limegreen', 'yellow')
palette(tropical)
par(pch=19)
data(diamonds)
set.seed(42)
small <- diamonds[sample(nrow(diamonds), 1000), ]
head(small)
##       carat       cut color clarity depth table price    x    y    z
## 49345  0.71 Very Good     H     SI1  62.5    60  2096 5.68 5.75 3.57
## 50545  0.79   Premium     H     SI1  61.8    59  2275 5.97 5.91 3.67
## 15434  1.03     Ideal     F     SI1  62.4    57  6178 6.48 6.44 4.03
## 44792  0.50     Ideal     E     VS2  62.2    54  1624 5.08 5.11 3.17
## 34614  0.27     Ideal     E     VS1  61.6    56   470 4.14 4.17 2.56
## 27998  0.30   Premium     E     VS2  61.7    58   658 4.32 4.34 2.67
bp <- ggplot(small,aes(color,carat))  + geom_boxplot(colour = "black",alpha=0.5,size = 2,width = 0.5)
bp <- bp + geom_jitter(width = 0.25,colour = "#3366FF")
bp <- bp + labs(x = "",y = "",title="The boxplot between color and carat") 

bp + JV.theme

bp <- ggplot(small,aes(color,carat))  + geom_violin(colour = "black",alpha=0.5,size = 2,width = 0.5)
bp <- bp + geom_jitter(width = 0.25,colour = "#3366FF")
bp <- bp + labs(x = "",y = "",title="The boxplot between color and carat") 

bp + JV.theme

eg<- small[,c(2,8:10)]
eg.m<- melt(eg)
## Using cut as id variables
head(eg.m)
##         cut variable value
## 1 Very Good        x  5.68
## 2   Premium        x  5.97
## 3     Ideal        x  6.48
## 4     Ideal        x  5.08
## 5     Ideal        x  4.14
## 6   Premium        x  4.32
bp <- ggplot(eg.m,aes(x=variable,y=value,fill=cut))  + geom_boxplot(colour = "black",alpha=0.5,size = 2,width = 0.5)

bp + scale_fill_manual(values = tropical) +JV.theme
